  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "She is empty, and void, and waste,.... The city of Nineveh, empty of inhabitants, being killed, or having fled; and stripped of all its treasures and riches by the enemies; its walls and houses demolished and pulled down, and laid in ruins, and become a heap of rubbish; See Gill on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Nahum 1:8",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Various words are here used to ascertain and confirm the thing; and there is an elegant play on words or likeness of sounds, which our language will not express: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the heart melteth; the heart of every inhabitant of Nineveh melted with fear at the approach of their enemies, their entrance into the city, and plunder of it; flowed like water, or melted like wax; see Psalm 22:14, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and the heart melteth; the heart of every inhabitant of Nineveh melted with fear at the approach of their enemies, their entrance into the city, and plunder of it; flowed like water, or melted like wax; see ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Psalm 22:14",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the knees smite together; like people in a fright, and when a panic has seized them; and as it was with Belshazzar, Daniel 5:6, ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "and the knees smite together; like people in a fright, and when a panic has seized them; and as it was with Belshazzar, ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Daniel 5:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", ",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and much pain is in all loins; like that of women in travail; or of persons in a sudden fright, which gives them a pain in their backs at once: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and the faces of them all gather blackness; like a pot, as the Targum adds; being in great distress and disconsolation, which make men appear in a dismal hue, and their countenances look very dark and gloomy; see Joel 2:6. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
